pride:
    play sound click
    choice:
        "The Bluehills Pride Parade! How exciting! Who might you bump into in the crowded streets?"
        "[Be proud in a vague and unspecified way (sponsored by the Dandelion and Burdock Corporation)] <span class='prompt'>[[-1 ACTION]]</span>" if (>= $stats.actions.value 1):
            play sound spendAction
            set data.game_map.inMap false
            add_stat actions -1
            run transition_black pride_street
            clear_dialog
        "<span class='prompt'>[[BACK]]</span>":
            jump game_map
    
    set data.global.prideAttended true
    play music chilling
    "A column of floats rolls through the high street. It's the last days of the war. The 3rd Armoured Divison breaking the cobbles of Kaiserstraße, fruity edition."
    "You watch for a few minutes. A float proudly displaying a huge statue of Wazzok the Warsheep passes by. She's not particularly related to pride, but people do seem very proud of her, so you join them in taking off your hat and crying as she passes by."
    "A group of police march past, then the detachment from the local Labour party. The Keeper of the Gate of Venus waves a flag advertising a private HRT clinic. Some guys in leather walk past, but are quickly followed up by an automobile advertising a service that replaces your lawn with a fake <span class='writtenText'>'no cutting required asbestos garden'</span>."
    clear_dialog
    "It is unclear if this automobile is part of the parade, or merely lost."
    clear_dialog
    "Despite the rather lacking procession, the crowd itself is in good spirits. People cheer, laugh, hug. Some wave weirdly complicated pride flags."
    if (roll pride_flag_yugogoslavia_orb orb 40):
        talk orb talk "That's not the actual pride flag, that's the flag of Königreich Jugogoslawien."
        clear_dialog
        run transition flag_yugogoslavia
        choice:
            talk orb talk "There's currently a shortage of yellow fabric, and so the factory producing pride flag just seems to be substituting orders with their curiously large backlog of Königreich Jugogoslawien heraldry."
            "That's horrible! How can I celebrate pride without being able to point at an arbitrarily chosen symbol and ascribe strict meanings to its many components!":
                talk orb talk "Well, you can do that with this flag, if you want. What do you want to know?"
                jump pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu
    else:
        wait 1000
    jump pride_sinner

pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The flag of Königreich Jugogoslawien flutters proudly through the streets, but not for the right reason."
        "What's the lightning shaped thing?":
            talk orb talk "The symbol of Bosnier."
            talk nasty talk "Bosnier? I hardly know her. Ha ha."
            jump pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu
        "Is that a wheel?":
            talk orb talk "Ah, that represents Trieste. The only surviving elector prince of the Holy Italian Empire."
            talk orb talk "Contractually they are not allowed to become emperor themselves, and as such traditionally elect a cool rock to the position of emperor every few years."
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "They're a semi-autonomous region within Königreich Jugogoslawien, which means the rock emperor is the emperor of an empire that hasn't existed for nearly one thousand years, elected by a region within a separate, lower ranking kingdom."
            jump pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu
        "Please explain the bird to me, Orb.":
            talk orb talk "The Finch of Peace. It's the flag of Thrace, site of some of the worst war crimes in history."
            jump pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu
        "Is that a castle. Is that a shepherd. What's going on?":
            talk orb talk "The Shepherd is a religious figure in central and south-east Europa."
            talk lovely talk "A false prophet..."
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "Beliefs vary, but the generally accepted mythology believes that the Divine once manifested itself on Earth in the form of a shepherd. He wandered the mountains searching for strays, both of the sheep and of the heathen variety."
            talk orb talk "Appearing suddenly at a pagan town to soothe their troubles, leaving them now in the light of the Divine."
            talk lovely talk "Saint Dawnsight could beat him in a fight... it would be easy for her..."
            clear_dialog
            if (roll pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu_shephered_orb orb 60):
                talk orb talk "In fact, many of the Shepherds believers claim they have seen the Divine at the top of the tallest peaks."
                choice:
                    talk orb talk "They're wrong, of course, what they're looking at is an optical illusion where one gazes upon their own shadow, ringed with sunlight, on the fog ahead of them. You silly creatures are so easily fooled..."
                    "I'm actually very difficult to fool.":
                        if $data.ghost.investor:
                            talk orb talk "You're actually incredibly easy to fool, Ghost. What little brain matter you have switches off the moment you hear the word 'investment'."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk orb talk "Either way, this phenomena is probably what sparked the stories of the Divine Shepherd in the first place."
                    "Tell me more. I'd like to know more about this subject.":
                        talk orb talk "Some tales involve a traveller woman named Mihaela. She was lost in the woods long long after the Italians executed the Shepherd, but he appeared to guide her still. He had her cast off her jewellery and led her home. As thanks she dedicated her life to spreading his story."
                        talk orb talk "There are two interpretations of this legend. Either <span class='writtenText'>'wealth is fleeting'</span> or <span class='writtenText'>'travellers are heathens who have to be converted or killed'</span>."
                    "Bored now. Let's stop discussing this.":
                        jump pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu
        "Is that a bird monster? Please tell me about the bird monster.":
            choice:
                talk orb talk "The two headed eagle of Serbia. One head looks west to Brenneburg and gloats, one head looks east to Musckovy and gloats."
                "What does the text mean?":
                    talk orb talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Hahahaha Serbia number one!'</span>, or words to that effect."
            jump pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu
        "That's a stick with a loop at the top.":
            talk lovely talk "You're right! Squeak squeak! How exciting!"
            clear_dialog
            talk nasty talk "We LIKE stick."
            talk lovely talk "We LIKE stick!"
            talk nasty talk "We LIKE stick."
            talk lovely talk "We LIKE stick!"
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk orb talk "Do you weirdos want an explanation or not?"
                "We LIKE stick!":
                    talk nasty talk "We LIKE stick."
                    talk lovely talk "We LIKE stick!"
                "We have no opinion on stick.":
                    talk nasty talk "No one asked."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk lovely talk "We LIKE stick!"
                    talk nasty talk "We LIKE stick."
                "We HATE stick!":
                    talk nasty talk "Oi, that stick is our friend, you fucking mug!"
                    talk lovely talk "What an awful woman she is... Ignore her, stick..."
                    clear_dialog
                    talk orb talk "Should we stop discussing this flag."
            jump pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu
        "What are the shields?":
            talk orb talk "Those are shields. They're just sort of there."
            jump pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu
        "Is that a town? What town is that?":
            talk orb talk "The Free City of Pristina. It's actually very expensive."
            talk nasty talk "LOL. Good one Orb."
            talk orb talk "What? No, I was being serious! It has a high cost of living due to a number of socio-economic factors you wouldn't understand!"
            jump pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu
        "I'll be honest ladies; I have no idea what that thing on the bottom is.":
            talk orb talk "That's the smaller two headed eagle of Nontamegro."
            talk orb talk "One head looks east to Serbia and complains about how it hates drinking sea water. The other head looks west to the sea and takes a big sip anyway. The historical records refuse to elaborate."
            jump pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu
        "What's with the knife?":
            talk nasty talk "Cool innit."
            talk lovely talk "So scary, and yet so alluring!"
            talk nasty talk "Thus is the beauty of the knife. The knowledge that another girl holds your life in her hands, the feeling of cold steel against your throat... the romance of gifting a girl a drop of your own blood... yes... truly the thinking girl's kink..."
            if $data.ghost.knifeplay:
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk nasty talk "You already know all that though don't you Ghost, you slut."
                    "When The Pulp Writer pricked me with her knife... raked it across my neck... [Nod] Hot...":
                        talk lovely talk "A transcendent experience..."
            clear_dialog
            talk orb talk "Uhuh. Anyhow, that's the heraldry of Ljubljana-Zagreb. Königreich Jugogoslawien annexed it from Brenneburg in the closing days of The Great War. No one really cared enough to make them give it back."
            jump pride_flag_yugogoslavia_menu
        "Thanks for telling me all about the flag, Orb. <span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>":
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk orb talk "You're welcome."
                "What does the *real* pride flag look like. I want to know if I feel represented by it or not.":
                    run transition flag_pride
                    talk orb talk "Yellow background. Red box. There is a lion in the middle."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk nasty talk "The lion represents homosexuality, on account of him looking kind of faggy. The box represents the blood soaked jailcell of society which traps the faggy lion. The yellow background? That's all piss, ladies. It represents us, the transexuals. Piss kink."
                        "I feel so represented right now.":
                            talk lovely talk "I don't! Horrible!"
                        "Sorry Nasty Girl but I'm only into normal things. I don't feel represented at all by this flag." if (!= $data.ghost.footGirl true):
                            run skip
                        "Sorry Nasty Girl but I'm only into normal things. I don't feel represented at all by this flag. There should be a bare foot on it." if (== $data.ghost.footGirl true):
                            run skip
                        "Transexuals are all perverts. [Look to the side as though there's someone there] I'm one of the good ones.":
                            add data.global.sideGlances 1
                            if (>= $data.global.sideGlances 3):
                                unlock_achievement scoops
                                play sound scoopsshutter
                                choice:
                                    talk scoops flash "You *are* one of the good ones, Ghost. One of my favourites!"
                                    "\\"Holy crackers! There *is* someone there!\\"":
                                        talk scoops talk "I've always been there, Ghost!"
                                        talk scoops talk "The names Scoops, Scoops McGee. Where there's a story there I'll be!"
                                        clear_dialog
                                        talk orb talk "CRYPTID CRYPTID CRYPTID THIS IS A CRYPTID."
                                        clear_dialog
                                        play sound scoopsshutter
                                        "Scoops McGee takes another photo of you with his camera."
                                        clear_dialog
                                        choice:
                                            talk scoops talk "Pleasure to meet you mam! But I better scram! Perhaps I'll see you again soon! Like the stars see the moon!"
                                            "\\"I love you Scoops McGee!\\"":
                                                set data.cryptids.loveScoops true
                                                "Scoops McGee is gone."
                                            "\\"Okay. Bye I guess.\\"":
                                                "Scoops McGee is gone."
                                complete_objective cryptids scoops
                                complete_quest cryptids cryptidsSuccess
                            else:
                                play sound scoopscharge
                                "The rustle of fabric. The soft hum of electricity."
                "I think I'm going to go proselytize to people about how they should be using the Jugogoslawien flag from the 18th century, since the new one was designed by someone who thinks 'balklander' is a blanket term.":
                    talk orb talk "Okay. You do that, Ghost."
            if (&& (objective_started? sinner woods) (!= (objective_completed? sinner woods) true) (> $stats.actions.value 4) (== $stats.day.value 4)):
                run transition pride_street
            jump pride_sinner

pride_sinner:
    clear_dialog
    if (&& (objective_started? sinner woods) (!= (objective_completed? sinner woods) true) (> $stats.actions.value 4) (== $stats.day.value 4)):
        "And then, as if he has always been there, a small man appears in front of you."
        clear_dialog
        play music bigmoney
        choice:
            talk pride talk "Here you go little lady! A Dandelion and Burdock and Suez Corporation pride pen, courtesy of the Dandelion and Burdock and Suez Corporation! <span class='writtenText'>'Proud to share a glass with the homosexuals!'</span>."
            "\\"Holy crackers! A free pen! Thank you sir!\\"":
                talk pride talk "Don't thank me, little lady! Thank the kind hearts at the Dandelion and Burdock and Suez Corporation! <span class='writtenText'>'Proud to share a glass with the homosexuals!'</span>"
            "\\"Aww gee, a free pen, just for me...\\" [Blush and swivel back and forth on your heel] \\"You sure know how to treat a girl right...\\"":
                talk pride talk "Just for you! Quite right, little lady!"
        clear_dialog
        if $data.ghost.lobsterGirl:
            "He scuttles away sideways, like a crab. You feel a strange fondness for your crustacean brother."
        else:
            "He scuttles away sideways, like a crab."
        play music chilling
        choice:
            "Looking down, you notice he never actually gave you the pen. Still, your brand loyalty has been increased by the positive interaction."
            "The Dandelion and Burdock and Suez Corporation is proud to share a glass with *me*, a homosexual... [Wipe a tear from your eye]":
                run skip
    else:
        run transition pride_sinner
        if $data.church.sinnerMet:
            talk sinner talk "Hello."
            clear_dialog
            "The Sinner has suddenly apparated in front of you, as women as ghostly as her are apt to do. She is smoking, as normal."
            if (|| (!= (objective_completed? sinner archive) true) (!= (objective_completed? sinner apartment) true) (!= (objective_completed? sinner woods) true)):
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk sinner talk "I have to say, Ghost, but since you failed to turn up I assumed perhaps you'd died."
                    "\\"No not yet. How about you?\\"":
                        "She scoffs."
                        clear_dialog
                        talk sinner talk "Sadly, I linger on still..."
                        if (roll pride_sinner_hurt_lovely lovely 40):
                            talk lovely talk "She was genuinely hurt when you didn't show up to see her, but she's trying to play it off as no big deal."
                        else:
                            wait 1000
                clear_dialog
            "The Sinner nods towards the parade."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk sinner talk "Feeling proud, Ghost?"
                "\\"I think so yes. At least eighty percent.\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "Oddly specific. What's got you feeling so-"
                "\\"I'm still working that out.\\"":
                    talk sinner talk "Eh. I'd not bother. No one feels proud, nor should they f-"
                "\\"I feel whatever the opposite of proud is. bLonp?\\"":
                    choice:
                        talk sinner talk "You feel bLonp."
                        "Proud upside down.":
                            talk orb talk "???"
                            talk nasty talk "You what love?"
                            talk lovely talk "I see it! bLonp! Proud upside down! A very astute observation, darling! Squeak squeak squeak!"
                            clear_dialog
                            talk sinner talk "I see, yes. I'm-"
            clear_dialog
            "A great honk interrupts The Sinner. A parade float pulled along by a truck passes by. She leaps into action."
        else:
            "You bump into a gangly woman. She looks about to growl at you but is interrupted by a great honk. A parade float pulled along by a truck passes by. She leaps into action."
        clear_dialog
        talk sinner talk "YOU FUCKERS! EAT SHIT!"
        clear_dialog
        play sound vasesmash
        animate #narrat-app narrat-screenshake
        "She hurls the bottle at the Dandelion and Burdock Corporations parade float. It smashes against the road, and no one even seems to notice it was launched in the first place."
        clear_dialog
        choice:
            talk sinner talk "Ah... well... never the less..."
            "\\"That seemed a little bit mean! I'm sure the Dandelion and Burdock Corporation has our best interests in mind!\\"":
                talk sinner talk "You think? Silly girl."
                if (roll pride_sinner_paramilitary_orb orb 20):
                    choice:
                        talk orb talk "Just last week they hired fascist paramilitaries to shoot over fifty local tribesmen who'd been settling near one of their Suez Canal warehouses."
                        "We all make mistakes, Orb.":
                            if (roll pride_sinner_wage_orb orb 20):
                                choice:
                                    talk orb talk "Their bosses monthly wage is higher than the GDP of most of the Middle East."
                                    "He's a hard worker, like me.":
                                        if (roll pride_sinner_water_orb orb 20):
                                            choice:
                                                talk orb talk "They own most of the water on the Arabian peninsula and make the locals buy marked up Dandelion and burdock soft drink to survive."
                                                "Well. It has nutrients and tastes of plants, so it's probably good for them.":
                                                    if (roll pride_sinner_navy_orb orb 40):
                                                        choice:
                                                            talk orb talk "They currently own the fifth largest navy on the planet, and primarily use it to blockade anyone who won't buy their products, while also not maintaining the ships and spewing engine oil and rust into the sea, killing the local marine life."
                                                            "And yet you participate in society too... curious...":
                                                                if (roll pride_sinner_future_orb orb 89):
                                                                    choice:
                                                                        talk orb talk "In 1936 they assassinate over twenty heads of state in the Middle East and Europa in an attempt to retain control of the Suez Canal so they can continue to cheaply export their soft drink to the eastern markets. The resulting power vacuums lead to multiple civil wars and over twenty-five million casualties between 1936 and 1954."
                                                                        "So what? That happened to me once and I was fine.":
                                                                            talk orb talk "Shut the fuck up."
                                                                        "Oh. Well, that's me told.":
                                                                            talk orb talk "Glad I could convince you. Eventually."
                                                                else:
                                                                    wait 1000
                                                            "Oh. Well, that's me told.":
                                                                talk orb talk "Sigh..."
                                                    else:
                                                        wait 1000
                                                "Oh. Well, that's me told.":
                                                    talk orb talk "Sigh..."
                                        else:
                                            wait 1000
                                    "Oh. Well, that's me told.":
                                        talk orb talk "Mhm."
                            else:
                                wait 1000
                        "Oh. Well, that's me told.":
                            talk orb talk "Mhm."
                else:
                    wait 1000
        clear_dialog
        choice:
            "The Sinner scowls."
            "\\"You don't look very proud right now. Is the parade not making you feel proud? I could ask them to try harder if you want?\\"":
                talk sinner talk "This isn't my usual scene. It's far too corporate, isn't it? Still. I was bored, and I thought it might be fun to shout at people for a bit."
        clear_dialog
        "As if summoned by the promise of being shouted at, a small man has appeared in front of you."
        clear_dialog
        play music bigmoney
        talk pride talk "Here you go ladies! Two Dandelion and Burdock Corporation pride pens, courtesy of the Dandelion and Burdock Corporation! <span class='writtenText'>'Proud to share a gla-'</span>"
        clear_dialog
        play sound punch
        "Before he can finish saying <span class='writtenText'>'glass with the homosexuals!'</span> The Sinner socks him in the face."
        clear_dialog
        talk sinner talk "FASCIST!"
        clear_dialog
        talk pride talk "Yowch! Wowzers! You've got quite the punch little lady! Tell me, have you ever wanted to buy some genuine bone-fide knuckle dusters?"
        if (roll pride_sinner_pasta_orb orb 40):    
            talk orb talk "They're made of dry pasta."
        clear_dialog
        talk sinner talk "I already have some. Don't make me show you them."
        if (roll pride_sinner_knuckle_orb orb 40):
            talk orb talk "No she doesn't."
        else:
            wait 1000
        clear_dialog
        talk pride talk "Oh oh oh oh oh oh! I see I see I see! Well, pleasure doing business with the two of you!"
        clear_dialog
        play sound footsteps
        if $data.ghost.lobsterGirl:
            "He scuttles away sideways, like a crab. You feel a strange fondness for your crustacean brother."
        else:
            "He scuttles away sideways, like a crab."
        clear_dialog
        play music chilling
        choice:
            talk sinner talk "I fucking hate pride parades. Why did I come here? I've got shit to do."
            "\\"I wanted a pen...\\"":
                talk sinner talk "Then perish."
                clear_dialog
                play sound footsteps
                "She storms off in a tizzy."
                if (roll pride_sinner_fine_lovely lovely 20):
                    talk lovely talk "She'll be fine, she just hurt her hand and is trying to cover up the fact she wants to cry over how bad it hurts with faux outrage."
                else:
                    wait 1000
            "\\"What kind of shit?\\"":
                if (quest_succeeded? sinner):
                    talk sinner talk "Buy more oestrodil leaf and poppers."
                else:
                    talk sinner talk "What else? The search. Absolution..."
                clear_dialog
                play sound footsteps
                "She storms off, leaving you behind."
                if (roll pride_sinner_hurt_lovely lovely 20):
                    talk lovely talk "She hurt her hand and is trying to cover up the fact she wants to cry over how bad it hurts by simply leaving as fast as possible."
                else:
                    wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    if (== (random 0 2) 0):
        run transition pride_librarian
        "Before you can recover from your encounter with the pale spectre, you walk straight into a woman holding a big sign."
        clear_dialog
        choice:
            talk librarian talk "Hello! Nice to see you here!"
            "\\"Do I know you?\\"":
                talk librarian talk "No, but I thought you looked bookish. Why haven't you visited the library?"
                clear_dialog
                "The wind flutters against her. She smells of lavender."
                clear_dialog
                if (roll pride_sinner_librarian_lovely lovely 20):
                    talk lovely talk "L'eau de bibliothèque! Methinks she's a librarian!"
                talk nasty talk "Wots 'libreys'?"
                if (roll pride_sinner_librarian_orb orb 60):
                    talk orb talk "The Bluehills Library was built in the brief period where Bluehills was once again capital of Anglia, after the Imperial occupation burnt down most of Lunden about a century ago. It's an impressive building, and a bit of a shame we haven't paid it a visit."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk librarian talk "We have books from basically every genre, from slop like <span class='writtenText'>'The Lovely Lady Handbook'</span> to genre changing fiction like <span class='writtenText'>'Sous la couronne noire ou : Meurtre d'épines'</span>!"
                    "\\"I didn't realise Bluehills had a library. I was never offered the chance to go there.\\"":
                        talk librarian talk "Do you only do what you're offered? Never do you seek out knowledge and new experiences of your own volition? Curious..."
                        clear_dialog
                        talk poppy talk "Look, I was really excited to write The Librarian and a bunch of books in the library. It was going to be this huge Imperial building built after Brennenburg inherited the Anglian throne, but before the revolution, a huge beautiful building, but it was out of scope and this games already three years late. I'm sorry."
                        clear_dialog
                        talk librarian talk "Anyway! I have to go advertise the library and my book group some more, it seems! Seeya!"
                        run transition pride_street
                        clear_dialog
                        "She disappears into the crowd."
    if (objective_started? writer pride):
        jump pride_writer_intro                                
    else:
        if (roll pride_sinner_writer_orb orb 80):
            talk orb talk "Someone is missing..."
            talk nasty talk "What."
            talk orb talk "Sorry. A vision came to me. I'll spare you the details."
            talk nasty talk "Shut fuck."
        else:
            wait 1000
        if $data.raven.met:
            jump pride_raven
        else:
            jump pride_writer_end_one
        
pride_writer_intro:
    run transition pride_aerial
    clear_dialog
    "You walk through the throng. The noise, the singing. The counter protest and a counter counter protest who chant <span class='writtenText'>'Alle babys abtreiben! Alle babys abtreiben!'</span>, for some reason."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "And then you smell it. A smell amongst the crowd that stands out... cigarettes and sickness..."
        "[Follow your nose]":
            play sound footsteps
            run transition pride_writer
            talk writer talk "Hello, Ghost."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                "Your nose is in her armpit. She is doing her best to look nonplussed."
                "[Stand up straight and pretend you weren't following her smell] \\"Hello.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "It is nice to see you again. I wasn't sure I'd bump into anyone worth talking to here."
                    clear_dialog
                    "She coughs into her hand and wipes it into her coat."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "Come, let us uhh, promenade."
        "[Promenade with The Pulp Writer]":
            choice:
                talk writer talk "So. What brings you to the parade, Ghost?"
                "\\"Pride, mostly.\\"":
                    choice:
                        talk writer talk "I see. Well. Happy pride, Ghost."
                        "[Look proud]":
                            run skip
                "\\"Mostly I'm here ironically.\\"":
                    talk writer talk "Ah, a true artist. It is much more enjoyable to do things you hate, isn't it?"
                "\\"I suspected I'd find you here and I've been wanting to find you because I like you.\\"":
                    "The Pulp Writer takes a small amount of damage from how hard she blushes, but she quickly recovers."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk writer talk "Ah, I see. Well you found me, didn't you?"
                        "[Nod] \\"I sniffed you out and tracked you down.\\" [Look stupidly proud of yourself]":
                            talk writer talk "Mmm. Impressive. I think. Mostly quite strange."
    clear_dialog
    "The crowds jostle you as you walk. It's not unfamiliar. You're used to this. The cis homos are waving their flags and enjoying their pens so much they're not really paying attention and keep standing on your toes. The Pulp Writer lights a smoke."
    if $data.raven.met:
        jump pride_raven
    else:
        jump pride_writer_end_one

pride_raven:
    run transition pride_aerial
    clear_dialog
    "Then, amongst the throng, the smell of engine oil and sweat. A recognisable silhouette, dark feathered wings uncoiling from a mountain."
    clear_dialog
    if (== $data.raven.interviewBad true):
        run transition pride_raven_kill
        talk raven talk "<span class='threat'>*You*.</span>"
        clear_dialog
        if (roll pride_raven_hankie_orb orb 40):
            talk orb talk "Oh dear... Red polkadot on white worn on the right hip? That's <span class='writtenText'>'Seeking vengeance, will not relent until I see blood...'</span> She must be serious about something..."
        else:
            talk orb talk "Oh shit."
        if (== (objective_completed? writer writerOne) true):
            clear_dialog
            "Your feet lift from the floor. Two great hands around your throat. You dangle in the grip of The Raven, more helpless and fluttering even than the coloured hankies tucked into her belt."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk raven talk "I saw your article about me, you speccy little cunt."
                "\\"D- did you like it?\\"":
                    "She snarls. A bead of spit lands on your cheek. Nice."
                "\\"I didn't do it?\\"":
                    "She snarls. A bead of spit lands on your cheek. Nice."
                "\\"S- Sorry! I was just doing my job!\\"":
                    "She snarls. A bead of spit lands on your cheek. Nice."
                "\\"Please don't kill me! Not at the pride parade! Think of the damage it would do to the reputations of all the brands sponsoring it!\\"":
                    "She snarls. A bead of spit lands on your cheek. Nice."
                "\\"I have a heart condition. If you hit me it'd be murder.\\"":
                    "She snarls. A bead of spit lands on your cheek. Nice."
                roll pride_raven_wife_orb orb 40 "Orb, do I have a pregnant wife I can talk about to get out of this mess?":
                    success "":
                        talk orb talk "Uh. No. Sorry."
                    failure "":
                        talk orb talk "Um. Sorry I have to go take the bins out. Seeya."
                        talk lovely talk "Um! Yes! Me too! I have to go watch the Stable Girl take my rubbish out too! Toodle ooh!"
                        talk nasty talk "Bunch of pussies. I'm with you till the end, Ghost."
                    clear_dialog
                    "The Raven snarls. A bead of spit lands on your cheek. Nice."
            clear_dialog
            talk raven talk "I told you not to write about me. We had a soldier's agreement on it."
            clear_dialog
            if (objective_started? writer pride):
                talk writer talk "Putain..."
                clear_dialog
                "The Pulp Writer tugs at The Raven's sleeve."
                clear_dialog
                talk writer talk "Miss, I'm excuse me about my colleague, she has brain damage, I think. Likely she forgot she promised not to write about you. I'll give you a cigarette if you don't kill her, oui?"
                clear_dialog
                "The Raven still looks like she wants to kill you, but she doesn't. She drops you to the floor. You land with the grace of a rat being dropped by a hyena."
                clear_dialog
                talk raven talk "Keep your cigarette."
                clear_dialog
                play sound footsteps
                run transition pride_street
                choice:
                    "The Raven growls, and storms off. The Pulp Writer scratches the back of her hand, recovering from the adrenaline rush of offering to give someone one of her cigarettes."
                    "\\"You saved me!\\"":
                        talk writer talk "If our dickhead boss finds out I let the new meat get killed after less than a week... well, he would not be my dickhead boss anymore. I would be fired, yes?"
            else:
                "The Raven tightens her grip. Your eyes bulge. This is so hot. You feel so horny. Or sleepy. Sleepy... sleepy..."
                unlock_achievement death_raven
                jump ending_credits
        else:
            clear_dialog
            "The Raven seems charged with violent energy. She's about to talk..."
            "And then she doesn't. She barges past you. A growl trailing behind her."
    elseif (|| (== $data.raven.threwWrench true) (== $data.raven.badEnd true)):
        clear_dialog
        run transition pride_raven_kill
        "The Raven seems charged with violent energy. She's about to talk..."
        "And then she doesn't. She barges past you. A growl trailing behind her."
    else:
        run transition pride_raven
        if $data.raven.saidYeen:
            choice:
                talk raven talk "Hello, squeaker."
                "\\"W-What!?\\"":
                    talk orb talk "Squeaker. It means mouse. It isn't a slur per sey, but it's still kind of a weird thing to say to someone you've never spoken to before, so people usually don't."
        else:
            talk raven talk "Ah, I thought it might be you."
        clear_dialog
        talk raven talk "Sniffed you out in the crowd. You've got quite the recognisable musk."
        clear_dialog
        if (objective_started? writer pride):
            talk writer talk "Why everyone is sniffing each other all the time these days? I don't get it... I don't get it..."
            clear_dialog
            "The Pulp Writer shakes her head and sighs."
            if (roll pride_raven_smell_orb orb 40):
                talk orb talk "They're just jealous that you two both have functioning senses of smell."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            "The Pulp Writer looks The Raven up and down. She appears a little scared of her, understandable, The Raven could probably kill her with a single hand, if she willed so. The Pulp Writer's gaze shifts to the coloured hankies tucked into The Raven's belt. She recognises *some* of them, but not all."
        else:
            "The Raven has dressed up pretty sharp today. She's aflutter with hankies, as unsuited as the word 'flutter' is for her."
        clear_dialog
        if (objective_completed? sinner woods):
            if (roll pride_raven_armpit_nasty nasty 40):
                talk nasty talk "That's the armpit one. We should hook this dyke up with The Sinner."
                if (roll pride_raven_armpit_lovely lovely 20):
                    talk lovely talk "Despite their somewhat similar views on guilt, The Raven would most likely despise The Sinner. The waifish goth does not know the meaning of the word 'sin'."
                else:
                    wait 1000
            else:
                wait 1000
        clear_dialog
        if (&& (== $data.raven.fixedRoof true) (quest_succeeded? fixHouse)):
            choice:
                talk raven talk "Hope the roof is working out for you. I couldn't have you catching your death of cold now, ay?"
                "\\"Thank you mam. You've made this little lady so happy...\\"":
                    run skip
        if $data.raven.goodEnd:
            run transition pride_raven_hug
            unlock_achievement hug
            "The Raven pulls you into her arms (big arms)."
            clear_dialog
            talk raven talk "About our chat the other day. Thank you, Ghost."
            if (roll pride_raven_grave_orb orb 20):
                talk orb talk "An epitaph etched into paintwork. Heidi, left to rest in the woods where she loved."
            else:
                wait 1000
            clear_dialog
            talk raven talk "It was stupid, keeping that old thing with me. Only looking at it so I could blame myself. Stupid...."
            talk raven talk "I suppose sometimes it takes someone else calling you out to make you realise quite how pointless your self loathing is, ay?"
            clear_dialog
            "She squints. <span class='golditalic'>Smiles</span>."
            clear_dialog
            talk raven talk "You're smarter than you look... sometimes."
            clear_dialog
            run transition pride_raven
            if (objective_started? writer pride):
                "The Pulp Writer has been watching this conversation, bereft of context, with confusion."
        clear_dialog
        if (objective_started? writer pride):
            talk writer talk "De toute façon, you two are what? Friends?"
            if (== $data.article.raven true):
                talk raven talk "I was the subject of this little lady's article."
                clear_dialog
                talk writer talk "Ah, I see. It is nice to meet you. Your exploits in the war were, how you say? Generic? But I appreciated the content never the less."
                clear_dialog
                "The Raven looks at you. Her face is stern, but not unhappy."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk raven talk "I was pleasantly surprised by the read. I was half expecting to have to... I don't know? Kill you?"
                    "\\"You read it!?\\"":
                        talk raven talk "I did. I mean, I didn't pay for the magazine, but I skimmed over it in the shop you know?"
                        clear_dialog
                        "The Pulp Writer mutters something under her breath."
                        if (roll pride_raven_rapiat_lovely lovely 20):
                            talk lovely talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Rapiat...'</span>"
                        else:
                            wait 1000
                    "\\"You can kill me if you want, mam, I'm down bad.\\"":
                        talk raven talk "Heh. I'll consider it."
            else:
                talk raven talk "Acquaintances. This little lady ran into me the other day. Stuck in my mind somehow."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk writer talk "Ah bon... she does have the habit of that, doesn't she..."
                    "\\"I can't tell if that's an insult or a compliment. Is it an insult?\\"":
                        "The two women make noncommittal noises."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk raven talk "So, what are you two ladies up to? Feeling proud?"
                "\\"We're going for a premonade!\\"":
                    talk writer talk "A promenade, Ghost..."
        else:
            choice:
                talk raven talk "What's brought you here today then?"
                "\\"I'm here to buy rainbow accessories for my motorcycle that I own.\\"" if $data.ghost.motorcycleLie:
                    talk raven talk "Yeah? Where's your ride?"
                    clear_dialog
                    talk nasty talk "Right in front of us, hopefully. Wahey."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk raven talk "Didn't bring it with you, huh? Pity."
                        "\\"No. Sorry. I'm just going for a walk with my slutty little feet today.\\"":
                            run skip
                "[Turn and look at the fuck off massive parade behind you] \\"Was that like a rhetorical question or?\\"":
                    "The Raven frowns."
                    if (roll pride_raven_rhetorical_lovely lovely 20):
                        talk lovely talk "She doesn't know what 'rhetorical question' means."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk raven talk "Eh?"
                        "\\"I'm going for a little walkies, mam.\\"":
                            run skip
                "\\"Walking. Wandering. You know how I am. I'm here for a walk.\\"":
                    if (roll pride_raven_know_lovely lovely 20):
                        talk lovely talk "She doesn't. Not really. She can guess, at best."   
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                    clear_dialog
        choice:
            talk raven talk "One of those eh? I'm here to pick up girls, personally."
            "\\"You can pick me up if you'd like.\\"":
                "The Raven shrugs."
                clear_dialog
                talk raven talk "Sod it, why not?"
                clear_dialog
                "She picks you up by the scruff of your neck, holding you a full foot off of the ground, at eye level with her."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk raven talk "How's that?"
                    "\\"Aha euuuuuuh thanksssss\\"":
                        if (objective_started? houseSnake hungry):
                            play sound hiss
                            "The Raven smirks. The smirk of a house snake cornering a bit of kipferl."
                        else:
                            "The Raven smirks. The smirk of a snake cornering whatever a snake eats in this setting."
                    "\\"Awooga! My tongue rolls out like a carpet and my eyes pop out. Big lady alert! Awooga! Ahem, you have a beautiful smile mam.\\"":
                        if (objective_started? writer pride):
                            "The Pulp Writer and The Raven look at each other. You sense movement behind you back."
                            if (roll pride_raven_shrug_orb orb 20):
                                talk orb talk "The Pulp Writer just shrugged and made a hand gesture implying you have brain damage."
                                if (roll pride_raven_hot_nasty nasty 40):
                                    talk nasty talk "She still finds you sexy though. More so, if anything, you little weirdo."
                                else:
                                    wait 1000
                            else:
                                wait 1000
                        else:
                            "The Raven makes a face."
                            if (roll pride_raven_brain_orb orb 20):
                                talk orb talk "She thinks you need to get outside more."
                            else:
                                wait 1000
                            clear_dialog
                            talk raven talk "It's less beautiful when it's biting into someone's tit. Or more. Who's to say."
                clear_dialog
                "The Raven drops you back down on the floor, takes off your beret, scruffles your hair, puts back on your beret, and then chuckles to herself, all without using a single full stop."
            "\\"That's bopper. The Nasty Girl who lives in my head told me dykes would be spitting in my mouth here, but so far no one has spat in my mouth, so I feel a bit let down.\\"":
                run transition_instant pride_raven_spit
                animate #narrat-app narrat-screenshake
                choice:
                    "Without a moments notice, The Raven spits at you."
                    roll pride_raven_spit_nasty nasty 40 "[Open wide]":
                        success "":
                            play sound plap
                            "Her saliva lands on your outstretched tongue with a wet 'plap'. It's warm. Tastes of spit and chewing tobacco."
                        failure ""
                            play sound plap
                            choice:
                                "Her saliva splatters against your face with a wet 'plap'. It's warm. You open your mouth a full three seconds later."
                                "\\"Oops.\\"":
                                    talk raven talk "Eh, better luck next time."
                clear_dialog
                run transition_instant pride_raven_lick
                if (objective_started? writer pride):
                    "The Raven smirks, and ruffles your hair. The Pulp Writer makes a face."
                    if (roll pride_raven_spit_lovely lovely 40):
                        talk lovely talk "Seeing the woman she wants to sleep with get spat on by a huge dyke has awakened something in her. She's a little wet."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                else:
                    "The Raven smirks, and ruffles your hair."
        if $data.raven.goodEnd:
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                "The Raven's eye catches something. She looks eager to get going."
                "\\"You know, I'm going through a whole 'going for a little walk' stint right now. I'm walkmoding. I've entered my 'walkies era'. What I'm saying is, <span class='writtenText'>'would you like to come walk with me tomorrow?'</span>\\"":
                    choice:
                        talk raven talk "Ehehe. Sorry Ghost, but if this parade is a success I'll be having a late night, if you get my meaning."
                        "[Squint] \\"I don't get your meaning.\\"":
                            if (roll pride_raven_clit_nasty nasty 20):
                                talk nasty talk "A Hyena's clitoris can become engorged and erect and when properly used, split small whining women in half like a melon."
                                talk orb talk "Delightful. Thanks for sharing."
                                clear_dialog
                            talk raven talk "Don't you worry."
                            clear_dialog
                            "She ruffles your hair."
                        "\\"I see. Having fuck with someone...\\"":
                            talk raven talk "Too right."
        clear_dialog
        if (objective_started? writer pride):
            talk raven talk "Well, enjoy your uhh... <span class='writtenText'>'pomee o granite'</span>, madamegazelles."
            clear_dialog
            play sound footsteps
            "The Raven winks at The Pulp Writer, nods at you, and wanders off."
            clear_dialog
            run transition pride_street
            talk writer talk "She said <span class='writtenText'>pommee o granite'</span>..."
            clear_dialog
            talk nasty talk "I'll pom your granite, Lovely Lady."
            talk lovely talk "W- what?"
        else:
            talk raven talk "Well enjoy your walk, Ghost. I'm going to go find someone to fuck."
            clear_dialog
            play sound footsteps
            "The Raven winks at you, and wanders off."
            clear_dialog
