            jump pride_menu
        "\\"Holy crackers, is that stall selling an <span class='writtenText'>'I'm on a milf diet'</span> / <span class='writtenText'>'I'm milf'</span> couples dress set?\\" [Rub your eyes] \\"It is!\\" [Rush over to the two dresses]" if (objective_started? writer pride):
            play sound footsteps
            "The Pulp Writer sighs, but decides to go along with your frivolity."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                "Just as you thought, this stall is selling two matching dresses. One with <span class='writtenText'>'I'm on a see milf diet'</span> written across it, and one with <span class='writtenText'>'I'm milf'</span> written across it."
                "\\"Just think how funny it'd be if we wore them together!\\" [Start laughing so hard that a bit of pee comes out]":
                    "The Pulp Writer's face is stone."
                    if (roll pride_menu_thinking_orb orb 20):
                        talk orb talk "She's thinking. She doesn't like it."
                    else:
                        wait 1000
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk writer talk "Ghost. I will be blunt. I am *not* wear a dress with <span class='writtenText'>'I'm milf'</span> written on it."
                        "\\"What? No, *I* was going to wear the <span class='writtenText'>'I'm milf'</span> dress!\\" [Sigh] \\"But alas, these dresses are to be left behind... they were too funny for this cruel world...\\"":
                            "The Pulp Writer is replaying the events that led her to this discussion in her head. Where did it go wrong?"
                        "\\"Understood.\\"":
                            run skip
            jump pride_menu
        "[Find a bench to sit on]" if (!= $data.pride.bench true):
            set data.pride.bench true
            add data.pride.writerEnjoyment 2
            play sound clothing
            if (objective_started? writer pride):
                run transition pride_bench
            else:
                run transition pride_bench_alone
            "The benches in the town centre aren't very comfortable. They're designed so homeless people can't sleep on them, homed people can't sit on them for too long without getting ass ache, and are all covered in rust and bird shit."
            if (objective_started? writer pride):
                play sound clothing
                "The Pulp Writer eyes the bench you're sat on suspiciously, but gives in. Her feet hurt."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    "She yawns, ever so gently."
                    "\\"Oh big yawn! Biggest yawn in the world!\\"":
                        talk writer talk "Yes... I'm tired..."
                    "\\"Oh normal yawn...\\"":
                        talk writer talk "Yes... I'm tired..."
                    "\\WAUUUUUU\\" [Make a fake yawn sound to put her off mid yawn]":
                        "The Pulp Writer shudders, her eyes flash open wide, wider than you've ever seen them. She is discombobulated to her core."
                        clear_dialog
                        talk writer talk "You... you cucked my yawn..."
                        clear_dialog
                        "Her face is so grumpy. Grumpier even than the first time you met her."
                        if (roll pride_menu_grumpy_lovely lovely 20):
                            talk lovely talk "She looks grumpy, but she found it a *bit* funny."
                        else:
                            wait 1000
                        clear_dialog
                        talk writer talk "Je suis fatigué..."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    "She looks it. Her nose scrunches up and her eyes droop closed."
                    "\\"Would you like to rest your head on me? I'm probably cleaner than the bench.\\" [Lie]" if (&& (!= $data.ghost.cleanClothes true) (!= $data.ghost.hadBath true)):
                        "The Pulp Writer looks you up and down. At best you are a lateral move, as far as hygiene is concerned. Regarding comfort however..."
                    "\\"Would you like to rest your head on me? I'm probably cleaner than the bench.\\"" if (&& (== $data.ghost.cleanClothes true) (== $data.ghost.hadBath true)):
                        run skip
                "She thinks about it."
                if (roll pride_menu_lean_lovely lovely 40):
                    talk lovely talk "She's embarrassed, but she *did* already fall asleep on you. The line has already been crossed."
                else:
                    wait 1000
                clear_dialog
                talk writer talk "Fine..."
                clear_dialog
                play sound clothing
                choice:
                    "She slumps against you. Not asleep, just resting. Her breathing is shallow and raspy, not helped by the cold air."
                    "[Stroke her nice hair]":
                        "She growls under her breath. She likes it."
                    "[Smell her nice hair]":
                        "The Pulp Writer's hair, unsurprisingly, smells of cigarettes."
                        clear_dialog
                        choice:
                            talk writer talk "Did you just smell my hair?"
                            "\\"Yes.\\"":
                                talk writer talk "Hmm."
                            "\\"No\\" [Lie]":
                                talk writer talk "Hmm."
                    "[Chew on her nice hair]":
                        choice:
                            talk writer talk "Why are you chewing my hair."
                            "[Attempt to speak with your mouth full of hair] \\"Nutrionch.\\"":
                                talk writer talk "Hmm."
                            "[Attempt to speak with your mouth full of hair] \\"I'mpf pnot.\\" [Lie]":
                                talk writer talk "Hmm."
                    "\\"Are you having a nice time?\\"":
                        talk writer talk "An okay time, I guess."
                        if (roll pride_menu_time_lovely lovely 20):
                            talk lovely talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Yes'.</span>"
                        else:
                            wait 1000
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    "The scrungly woman seems to sink into you. Your wings are so so comfortable to rest one's head against..."
                    "[Hold her hand]":
                        "She squeezes your hand back. Her fur isn't soft, but it's nice anyway. You stroke it."
                        "She grumbles. Sniffles. Breathes your smell."
                clear_dialog
                wait 4000
                "You rest for a while, until she jolts up. She had nodded off."
                clear_dialog
                talk writer talk "Trop somnolent... trop froid pour dormir ici..."
                clear_dialog
                "She clears her throat. It's claggy."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk writer talk "Okay. Enough sitting... it is making me lethargic, and I don't fancy catching the death of me out in this cold."
                    "[Get up]":
                        play sound clothing
                        run transition pride_cathedral
                        jump pride_menu
            else:
                choice:
                    talk orb talk "Having fun, Ghost?"
                    "Yes!":
                        talk orb talk "Hmm. Me too, I suppose. I feel pretty proud of being an Orb right now..."
                        
                    "No.":
                        talk orb talk "Oh. I suppose most of the crowd looks less lonely than you, don't they?"
                        talk orb talk "I'm having an okay time, I suppose. I feel pretty proud of being an Orb right now..."
                talk orb talk "It makes me happy seeing so many people enjoying each other's company. Strange. Will muse on this later..."
                clear_dialog
                choice:
                    talk orb talk "I'd prefer not to think about it right now. Emotions still scare me. Let us move ever onwards."
                    "[Get up]":
                        play sound clothing
                        run transition pride_cathedral
                        jump pride_menu
        "[Look at The Pulp Writer]" if (objective_started? writer pride):
            "She's so strange."
            "Her face is blank, save the slight motion of her chewing the inside of her mouth, but her eyes seem so curious about the world around her. Ambivalent, but curious."
            "She doesn't seem to notice you watching her, she's too distracted by the commotion."
            clear_dialog
            if (roll pride_menu_gone_lovely lovely 60):
                talk lovely talk "She would have left a long time ago if you were not here."
            else:
                wait 1000
            if (roll pride_menu_pawris_orb orb 40):
                talk orb talk "She is reminded of the winter markets in Frankreich."
                talk orb talk "They were louder than this, but less shrill. There was an air of peace to them. She can't argue that this parade does not have an energy, but it's not one she particularly gels with."
                talk orb talk "A protest with no real demands. It means little to claim pride, she thinks. The *truly* proud would take up arms and fight."
                if (roll pride_menu_fight_orb orb 60):
                    talk orb talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Even so...'</span> she thinks. <span class='writtenText'>'Fight or no, the world gets no better... perhaps this is all there is?'</span>."
                clear_dialog
            else:
                wait 1000
            jump pride_menu
        "\\"Bored now.\\" <span class='prompt'>[[MOVE ON]]</span>" if (objective_started? writer pride):
            jump pride_writer_end_two
        "\\"Bored now.\\" <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>" if (!= (objective_started? writer pride) true):
            play sound spendAction
            talk orb talk "Maybe next years will be better?"
            talk lovely talk "More refined. Wine and waiters, mayhap?"
            talk nasty talk "It'll bop. We'll be in our whore era by then, just you follow my advice more often, Ghost."
            jump goToGameMap

pride_writer_end_two:
    if (<= $data.pride.writerEnjoyment 1):
        talk writer talk "This is a bit shit, isn't it, Ghost? I feel straighter for coming here."
    else:
        if (<= $data.pride.writerEnjoyment 2):
            talk writer talk "It's quite loud, Ghost. I'm done here if you are."
        else:
            talk writer talk "That was... surprisingly fun. Not my usual scene... but thank you, Ghost..."
    clear_dialog
    "She scratches the inside of her ear with her pride pen, sniffs it, and then throws it down a drain."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "So. About yesterday, Ghost."
        "\\"What about it?\\"":
            run skip
        "\\"It was cute, I think.":
            "The Pulp Writer blushes. Her blushes are blue. She's cold and pale and sickly."
        "\\"Sorry you fell asleep on me. I'm such a fucking predator... the evil voice in my head is right...\\"":
            talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>was there ever any doubt, creep?</span>"
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Eh? No... no... it was nice..."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "I've been alone for a while, Ghost. It's been a long time since I was with another woman. I wanted to apologise, in case I came on too strong yesterday. I'd blame the drugs, but that would be to absolve myself of my thorns..."
        "\\"No it was okay, I liked it. Hence why I kissed you. Mwah.\\" [Kiss her on the forehead]":
            "She growls, and then mumbles under her breath."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Je vais te tuer..."
            if (roll writer_end_embarrassed_lovely lovely 40):
                talk lovely talk "She's so embarrassed, bless."
            else:
                wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    play sound footsteps
    "She hurries on down a street. The movement keeps her warm."
    "You pass by Bluehills theatre. <span class='writtenText'>'Unedited Footage of a Teatime'</span> is playing, but The Pulp Writer seems uninterested in it. She's distracted by a particularly gaudy automobile."        
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "I hate automobiles. A blight on the Divine. What's wrong with trains, you bourgie scum?"
    clear_dialog
    clear_dialog
    play sound thud
    "She kicks the automobiles tyre. It wobbles, ever so slightly."
    if (roll writer_end_kick_orb orb 20):
        talk orb talk "That was about as hard as she could kick it. Her bones are very brittle, and her muscles very small."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "Shit parking too. Imbécile."
        "\\"Train good automobile bad.\\"":
            talk lovely talk "Train good automobile bad."
        "\\"Eh. Automobiles are fine.\\"":
            talk writer talk "They're not. They're shit. Waste of space and resources. We voted to have all drivers shot back in the CSCPCSEIFECAN."
            if (roll writer_end_miss_lovely lovely 40):
                talk lovely talk "There's an unspoken sigh in her voice. She misses the CSCPCSEIFECAN, sometimes. She enjoyed arguing with them. Sometimes even enjoyed their company. Those days are gone now. No more fistfights  in the coffee house..."
            else:
                wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The Pulp Writer throws her cigarette to the ground and stubs it out with her foot. She immediately lights another one."
        roll writer_end_smash_one_nasty nasty 60 "[Attempt to impress the scrungly woman by picking up the big iron bar and smashing the automobiles window with it]":
            success:
                jump pride_writer_smash_one
            failure:
                jump pride_writer_smash_failure
        "\\"I just want you to know I was considering smashing this automobile up with the iron beam, to impress you. I'm not going to do it though, but it's the thought that counts, I think.\\" [Nod proudly]":
            "The Pulp Writer chuckles. <span class='goldItalic'>Smiles</span>."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Yes. Well. Consider me very impressed."
            jump pride_writer_kiss

pride_writer_smash_one:
    play sound vasesmash
    animate #narrat-app narrat-screenshake
    set data.global.smashedCar true
    "You slam the iron bar into the window. The glass shatters."
    if $data.global.sawReflection:
        if (roll writer_end_smash_one_reflection_nightmare nightmare 20):
            talk nightmare talk "<span class='nightmare'>Still upset about seeing your reflection the other day? Smashing up a window won't change anything, idiot.</span>"
        else:
            wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The Pulp Writer raises an eyebrow wryly. She wasn't expecting you to do that, but now that you have... she's excited."
        roll writer_end_smash_two_nasty nasty 60 "[Smash the automobiles bonnet with the big metal bar]":
            success
                jump pride_writer_smash_two
            failure
                jump pride_writer_smash_failure
        "\\"I think I had better stop, my arms hurt a lot. I'm very weak.\\"":
            choice:
                talk writer talk "Fair enough, Ghost. I was very much impressed by the carnage you did committed to, though."
                "[Beam at her with a big dorky smile. Look stupidly proud of your achievement]":
                    "She <span class='goldItalic'>smiles</span> back."
    jump pride_writer_kiss

pride_writer_smash_two:
    play sound metalcrash
    animate #narrat-app narrat-screenshake
    "The Pulp Writer cracks a smile. This might be the first time you've ever seen that."
    if (roll writer_end_smash_two_wait_orb orb 80):
        set data.writer.end_orbWarning true
        talk orb talk "NO NO NO. WAIT. STOP."
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "The Pulp Writer watches you expectantly. An uncharacteristic grin growing on her face. She's so pretty it makes you blush."
        roll writer_end_smash_three_nasty nasty 60 "[Hit the automobile one more time, for old times sake]":
            success:
                play sound metalcrash
                animate #narrat-app narrat-screenshake
                "You whack the automobile on the door. The noise echoes though the street."
                jump pride_writer_sequel
            failure:
                jump pride_writer_smash_failure
        "\\"I think I had better stop, my arms hurt a lot. I'm very weak.\\"":
            choice:
                talk writer talk "Fair enough, Ghost. I was very much impressed by the carnage you did committed to, though."
                "[Beam at her with a big dorky smile. Look stupidly proud of your achievement]":
                    "She <span class='goldItalic'>smiles</span> back."
            jump pride_writer_kiss

pride_writer_smash_failure:
    play sound punch
    run transition_pain
    choice:
        "You slam the iron bar into the window. It bounces off bonks you on the nose. You fall to the floor in a heap."
        "\\"Yowch! That hurt a LOT!\\"":
            talk writer talk "Mmm. I bet it did. Silly girl."
            clear_dialog
            "The Pulp Writer kneels beside you and brushes her hand across your cheek. She chuckles, very quietly."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                talk writer talk "Poor thing."
                "\\"Am I going to die? Woe is me...\\"":
                    talk writer talk "You're fine. You seem perhaps a little delirious and empty headed, but that isn't out of the ordinary for you, if I'm being honest."
                    clear_dialog
                    "She ruffles your hair."
                    clear_dialog
                    choice:
                        talk writer talk "I was *very* impressed."
                        "[Smile dorkily]":
                            "She chuckles. <span class='goldItalic'>Smiles</span>."
                        "Don't mock me I could kill you instantly with my iron beam.":
                            "She chuckles. <span class='goldItalic'>Smiles</span>."
                            clear_dialog
                            talk writer talk "I bet."
                        "Don't mock me I could kill you instantly with my iron beam.\\" [Realise that's really inappropriate given her backstory] \\"I mean uh um uh\\"" if (== $data.writer.backstory true):
                            "She chuckles. <span class='goldItalic'>Smiles</span>."
                            clear_dialog
                            talk writer talk "I bet."
    jump pride_writer_kiss

pride_writer_sequel:
    clear_dialog
    "You can feel something on the back of your neck. A bite? A cold, icy presence?"
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk landlady talk "Y- YOU."
        "[Tug at your collar] \\"Gulp, uh oh!\\" [Drop the iron bar]":
            "Your Landlady has emerged from the movie theatre. Apparently that final hit was loud enough to break through the serene ballroom soundtrack of <span class='writtenText'>'Unedited Footage of a Teatime'</span>."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Hmm? Who is this?"
            clear_dialog
            talk landlady talk "Who am I? I'm this hooligans landlady, and this is my automobile!"
            talk landlady talk "Honestly, town has been full of your sort all day, and it's made the school run hel! Now I try to enjoy a motion picture and come outside to find my automobile in tatters!"
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "Our type? At least we're mammals you fucking parasite. Dans un monde juste tu serais ditch filler already!"
            clear_dialog
            "Your Landlady shoots daggers from her eyes, killing both you and The Pulp Writer instantly. Not literally, obviously."
            clear_dialog
            talk landlady talk "You will be hearing from my lawyer, young lady."
            clear_dialog
            play sound caraway 3
            "Your Landlady climbs into her dented automobile and drives off, spitting smoke out of her exhaust in an attempt to suffocate the two transexuals she's left behind."
            "As the growling noise of the automobile disappears, silence hangs heavy over you. Your arms are sore from their, to be honest, meagre exertion. The wind is cold. It bites."
            clear_dialog
            choice:
                "Then, something strange. The Pulp Writer laughs. Not a quiet laugh, a big one. She's practically cackling."
                "\\"Oh shit, are you okay? Is this one of those things you only do when you're *very* distressed? Should I do the Heimlich manoeuvre?\\"":
                    "The Pulp Writer tries to respond, but can't she wipes a tear from her eye."
                "[Laugh with her]":
                    "You sort of force a laugh in a very 'this option was in [square brackets]' sort of way. Ha ha ha."
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "J'ai..."
    clear_dialog
    "She laughs again."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "J'ai mal au ventre..."
        "[Nod like you understood that] \\"Hmm yeah me too.\\"":
            talk writer talk "I... sorry. I'm not sure what came over me. She just looked so angry and you... you looked like you'd seen a... well, a ghost. Aha. Quite the scene... tres bon... tres bon..."
    talk writer talk "Ahhh... that was tres bon... Very funny... I haven't laughed that hard since... well, I haven't."
    clear_dialog
    "The Pulp Writer sits in the gutter, catching her breath. Occasionally she giggles. Less and less each time, until she returns to energy saving mode."
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "Tell me, how do you feel about sequels, Ghost?"
        "\\"I like them a normal amount.\\"":
            talk writer talk "Good. It is good to like things a normal amount, I think, when the thing in question is so benign."
        "\\"I like them. I think there should only be one story that goes on forever. About superheroes, preferably.\\"":
            talk writer talk "Hmm. I disagree with that, to be honest. It sounds trite. Still, I am glad the idea of a sequel does not fill you with artistic venom."
        "\\"I hope this game gets one send money to Das Poppy Und Mia Kunstkollektiv to get a sequel folks.\\"":
            talk poppy talk "Are you fucking joking do you know how many years of my life writing this game took from me? Fuck you. Suck my dick. I'm doing something else with my time."
            clear_dialog
            talk writer talk "I uhh... I am not sure I understand you, this is an Anglian expression, I assume? But you are open to the concept of sequels, I gather?"
        "\\"I don't like them.\\"":
            talk writer talk "No, me neither. They are a symptom of cultural decay. That said..."
    choice:
        talk writer talk "Watching you smash up Your Landlady's automobile... it filled me with a great sense of uhhhh... how you say?"  
        "[Nod] \\"Ennui.\\"":
            talk writer talk "No. There are more emotions than just ennui, Ghost. I was thinking of... inspiration, passion maybe?"
        "\\"Inspiration?\\"":
            talk writer talk "Inspiration, yes. Very good."
        "\\"Passion?\\"":
            talk writer talk "Passion, yes. Very good."
        "\\"Boner. It gave you a hard on?\\"":
            talk writer talk "Well, it was quite sexy of you, but no, I don't have the blood flow for that. I was thinking of... inspiration, passion maybe?"
    clear_dialog
    talk writer talk "A single phrase came to mind... <span class='writtenText'>'Sous la couronne noire ou : Meurtre d'épines'</span>"
    if (roll writer_end_sequal_crown_orb orb 20):
        talk orb talk "<span class='writtenText'>'Under the Black Crown or: Murder of Thorns'</span>"
    else:
        wait 1000
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        talk writer talk "What do you think, Ghost?"
        "\\"Let us take up the fallen thorns and drive them into the black crown. Let us pulverise it into dust.\\"":
            talk writer talk "Ouiais. Let us."
        "\\"Lady cute. So so scruggly but oh so pretty.\\" [Scruffle The Pulp Writer's hair]":
            "The Pulp Writer rolls her eyes. A <span class='golditalic'>smile</span> flickers on her face. She knows you saw it."
        "\\"Train good automobile bad.\\"":
            talk writer talk "Ouais. You are right, Ghost."
    clear_dialog
    "She <span class='goldItalic'>smiles</span> at you. A tear in the corner of one eye. She just looks at you for a moment. Silent."
    jump pride_writer_kiss

pride_writer_kiss:
    clear_dialog
    choice:
        "A zeppelin crawls through the sky overhead. A vapour trail left behind like snail slime across a living room floor. Grey. The same colour as her eyes. She leans in and kisses you."
        "[Kiss her back] <span class='prompt'>[[CONTINUE]]</span>":
            play sound spendAction
            complete_objective writer pride
            complete_quest writer writerSuccess
            set data.ending.presentWriter true
            jump goToGameMap